# Roofing SlatePress design system (roofingslatepress-com-site repo)

This rule encodes the canonical brand tokens for **roofingslatepress.com**. It is a Phase-1 splash placement page in the SlatePress portfolio - same minimal token set shared across all vertical splash pages, so when they graduate to full landers (or get rolled into a vertical-specific full design pass), the design system is already in place.

The source of truth for these tokens is the `:root` block at the top of `index.html`. If they ever drift, this rule should be updated to match - the live file wins.

## Canonical tokens (splash-tier set)

```css
:root{
  --bg:#FFFFFF;             /* page canvas - pure white */
  --ink:#0A0A0A;            /* primary text, near-black */
  --ink-soft:#3A3D42;       /* secondary text */
  --slate:#6B6A73;          /* tertiary text */
  --rule:#E5E7EB;           /* default 1px borders */
  --blue:#2563EB;           /* PRIMARY brand blue - logo "/" + primary CTAs */
  --blue-deep:#1D4ED8;      /* hover state */
  --blue-soft:#EFF3FF;      /* tinted backgrounds, badges */
}
```

## Type stack

**Inter only.** Single sans-serif throughout.

```css
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Cardinal rules for roofingslatepress-com-site

- **Pure white canvas (`--bg #FFFFFF`).** Splash placement pages are quiet and minimal - they're a placeholder until the vertical graduates. Don't add gradient backgrounds, hero imagery, or paper tints unless promoting this site to a full lander.
- **Brand blue (`--blue` #2563EB) is the one accent.** Logo `/`, primary CTAs, focus rings, at most one emphasis moment per viewport.
- **Splash content only.** This site exists to (a) hold the domain, (b) present a coming-soon / waitlist message, (c) capture interest if any. Multi-section landers with services/pricing/comparison/founders bands belong in the full-lander tier (see `plumbingslatepress-com-site` for the full template), not here.
- **No new hex codes.** Stick to the 8-token set above. If a real product launch is happening on this domain, raise the design-system question first - probably means promoting to a full-lander token set (paper tints + extended type), not adding ad-hoc hexes here.
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**

## When designing or reviewing UI in this repo

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill. When it fires:
1. Ask "What are we designing today?"
2. On the answer "roofingslatepress.com" or any edit in this repo, load the tokens above.
3. Apply universal taste principles on top.
4. Produce code that references the brand's variable names (`--blue`, `--ink`, `--bg`) directly - never invent token names.

## Promoting to a full lander

When this domain graduates from splash-tier to full lander (i.e., the trade vertical lights up and gets its own paid pricing card, services pages, comparison tables, etc.), the design-system tokens need to expand from this 8-token set to the full lander set. See `plumbingslatepress-com-site/.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` for the canonical full-lander template (paper-tinted bg variants, --max width, additional rule strokes, blue-bright variant). Don't shortcut by adding ad-hoc hexes to the splash set - rebuild the `:root` block from the full template.
